Package uk.gov.gchq.gaffer.operation.impl.add

Class AddElements

  • java.lang.Object
    • uk.gov.gchq.gaffer.operation.impl.add.AddElements
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Closeable, AutoCloseable, Input<Iterable<? extends Element>>, MultiInput<Element>, Operation, Validatable
    public class AddElements
extends Object
implements Validatable, MultiInput<Element>
    An AddElements operation is a Validatable operation for adding elements. This is a core operation that all stores should be able to handle. This operation requires an Iterable of Elements to be added. Handlers should throw an OperationException if unsuccessful. For normal operation handlers the operation View will be ignored.
